aithfully<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Rescind Eason Chan's Honorary Degree&quot;<br />\n收返個學位通常用 Revoke<br />\n<br />\n第一段原文<br />\n<span class=\"orange\">In 2014, Eason Chan was awarded an honorary doctorate degree by Kingston University for his achievement in his music career. Unfortunately, fast-forward to 2021, the current values and political stance Eason Chan displays on social media stand against everything Kingston University represents.<br />\n<br />\n</span><br />\n第一句就 passive voice, 無乜力咁, 可以試下一開波就指住︰係「你」頒俾個名譽學位佢:<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"violet\">Your University awarded an honorary doctorate degree to Eason Chan in 2014, recognising his achievements in the music industry. </span><br />\n<br />\n後半句係Kingston 新聞稿黎, 官方講點解俾呢個學位佢<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.kingston.ac.uk/news/article/1216/24-jan-2014-cantopop-superstar-eason-chan-takes-to-the-stage-to-receive-honorary-degree-from-kingston-university/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kingston.ac.uk%2Fnews%2Farticle%2F1216%2F24-jan-2014-cantopop-superstar-eason-chan-takes-to-the-stage-to-receive-honorary-degree-from-kingston-university%2F&d=qOmKSCuv03M2cFfeadZVWpzZIytzq3Xhz5Kp58Ixet8%3D&h=a27dbc34\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.kingston.ac.uk/news/article/1216/24-jan-2014-cantopop-superstar-eason-chan-takes-to-the-stage-to-receive-honorary-degree-from-kingston-university/</a><br />\n<br />\n第二句 似乎唔係好明顯佢做咗乜 <br />\n又點違反 everything Kingston represents <br />\n咁 Kingston represents 乜?<br />\n我見下第二段邊果度有講 Nike etc concern ... forced labour<br />\n其實呢樣就係其中一樣<br />\n佢有個 Statement on the Modern Slavery Act<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.kingston.ac.uk/aboutkingstonuniversity/modern-slavery-statement/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kingston.ac.uk%2Faboutkingstonuniversity%2Fmodern-slavery-statement%2F&d=qOmKSCuv03M2cFfeadZVWpzZIytzq3Xhz5Kp58Ixet8%3D&h=1ad2d214\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.kingston.ac.uk/aboutkingstonuniversity/modern-slavery-statement/</a><br />\n<br />\nThis Statement is designed to satisfy the requirements of Part 6 Section 54 of the Modern Slavery Act (2015)(the Act).<br />\n<br />\nThe University's Ethics Policy states our commitment to the highest standards of ethical conduct in all our activities, along with making continuous improvements in this area. The University does not engage in, or condone, the practices of human trafficking, slavery or forced labour.<br />\n<br />\n講到明大學 policy 會為維持最高嘅 ethical standard, 唔參與唔接受human trafficking, slavery or forced labour. (有關新彊嘅指控三樣都有)<br />\n<br />\n如果係咁第二句就 可以直入指呢位傑出校友其實係反對你呢啲 ethics, 唔參與唔接受強迫勞動 policy: <br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"violet\">But as a distinguished Kingston alumni he seemed to be against your University's explicit commitment &quot;to the highest standards of ethical conduct in all our activities&quot;, and the policy of not to &quot;engage in, or condone, the practices of human trafficking, slavery or forced labour.</span><br />\n<br />\n&quot;fast forward&quot; 其實無乜意思, 其實都唔駛講<br />\n<br />\npolitical stance  人人可以唔同, 你插佢呢個無乜用, 但上邊啲 ethical value 就唔同, 可以普世啲...."},{"pid":"4dc19bd0d8553dfa37acc0aa7cef5886e0323231","tid":2463024,"uid":189150,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"c0772c94f4f519adb414298e23a6c36926054485","tid":2463024,"uid":67963,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-26T19:44:06.000Z","msg":"(齋論英文, 想寫得有力啲, 請其他巴絲賜教)<br />\n<br />\n睇開首 + 第一段先<br />\n基本野先,  formal 開首用 Dear sir/madam<br />\n最後應該用 yours faithfully<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Rescind Eason Chan's Honorary Degree&quot;<br />\n收返個學位通常用 Revoke<br />\n<br />\n第一段原文<br />\n<span class=\"orange\">In 2014, Eason Chan was awarded an honorary doctorate degree by Kingston University for his achievement in his music career. Unfortunately, fast-forward to 2021, the current values and political stance Eason Chan displays on social media stand against everything Kingston University represents.<br />\n<br />\n</span><br />\n第一句就 passive voice, 無乜力咁, 可以試下一開波